{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01PhE536qg9RF4HpCXB88ZGA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017A7vhbWS7NcqyVNpsGBRfq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Polenta with Wild Mushrooms.generated.18.txt","content":"Polenta with Wild Mushrooms\n\nCreamy polenta is an Italian comfort food that deserves a place in every home cook's rotation. When topped with\nsautéed wild mushrooms in a rich garlic and herb sauce, it becomes an elegant dish worthy of special occasions.\nThis recipe works wonderfully as a vegetarian main course or as a sophisticated side dish alongside roasted meats.\nThe beauty of polenta lies in its versatility and the fact that it can be prepared several hours ahead. The mushroom\nragù improves with time, developing deeper flavors as it sits. This is the kind of dish that warms both body and soul\non cool autumn and winter evenings.\n\nIngredients (serves 4)\n\nFor the Polenta:\n4 cups vegetable broth\n1 cup whole milk\n1 cup polenta (cornmeal)\n4 tbsp butter\n2 oz Parmesan cheese, grated\nSalt and white pepper\n\nFor the Mushrooms:\n1.5 lbs mixed wild mushrooms (cremini, shiitake, oyster), sliced\n4 cloves garlic, minced\n2 shallots, minced\n1 cup dry white wine\n1 cup vegetable or chicken broth\n1/2 cup heavy cream\n3 tbsp olive oil\n2 tbsp fresh thyme leaves\n2 bay leaves\nSalt and pepper to taste\nFresh parsley for garnish\n\nInstructions\n\n1. For polenta: Bring broth and milk to boil in large pot\n2. Whisk polenta slowly into liquid to avoid lumps\n3. Reduce heat to low and stir constantly for 30-40 minutes\n4. Polenta should pull away from sides of pot\n5. Stir in butter and Parmesan, season with salt and pepper\n6. For mushrooms: Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat\n7. Add mushrooms in batches, cooking until golden and moisture evaporates\n8. Add garlic and shallots, cook 2 minutes more\n9. Deglaze pan with white wine, scraping up browned bits\n10. Add broth, thyme, and bay leaves\n11. Simmer 20 minutes until flavors meld\n12. Stir in cream and season with salt and pepper\n13. Spoon polenta onto plates and top with mushroom ragù\n14. Garnish with fresh parsley\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":791,"cache_read_input_tokens":82412,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":791},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9a7c1af-9751-4310-853d-8c46d3069c79","uuid":"c8afe21b-7f1d-4f8f-afbc-919b094de1e7"}
