{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_018RN7qxXq49nR7qG2tYYHUE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015hm7u3ik38QWqT5YZgmkY6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Risotto with Asparagus.generated.18.txt","content":"CHAPTER 12                          p. 156-157\n\nRISOTTO WITH\nASPARAGUS\n\nPrep time: 15 min | Cook time: 20 min | Serves 4-5\n\nIngredi ents\n\n300g Arborio rice\n1 lb fresh asparagus, trimmed\n1 medium onion, finely d-\niced\n2 cloves garlic, minced\n1 liter warm vegetable br-\noth (approx)\n200ml dry white wine\n100g Parmesan cheese, grat-\ned\n50g butter\n2 tbsp olive oil\nSalt & pepper to taste\nZest of 1 lemon\nSplash of cream (optional)\n\nPreparation\n\n1. Heat broth in separate pot, keep warm\n   throughout cooking\n2. Cut asparagus tips from stalks; cut st-\n   alks into 1-inch pieces\n3. Heat olive oil & butter in large saucepan\n4. Add onion & garlic, sauté until transluc-\n   ent (2-3 min)\n5. Add rice, stir continuously for 1 minute\n   to lightly toast grains\n6. Deglaze with wine, stir until almost comp-\n   letely absorbed\n7. Begin adding warm broth 1 ladle at a tim-\n   e, stirring constantly\n8. Wait until each addition absorbed before\n   adding next (approx 18-20 min total)\n9. Add asparagus pieces halfway through co-\n   oking\n10. Finish with asparagus tips in last 2 min\n11. Rice should be creamy, not mushy - test\n   grain texture\n12. Remove from heat, stir in butter & Parm-\n   esan cheese\n13. Season with salt, pepper, lemon zest\n14. Add cream if desired for richer texture\n15. Serve immediately while hot\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":660,"cache_read_input_tokens":84781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":660},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"stan